396
00:29:00,271 --> 00:29:02,406
All of us are excited to do our best

397
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:05,843
for this episode, so watch out!

398
00:29:05,844 --> 00:29:07,077
Just reading the script,

399
00:29:07,078 --> 00:29:08,879
you can tell the story is really good

400
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:11,015
and easy for people to follow.

401
00:29:11,349 --> 00:29:13,350
But what really stands out

402
00:29:13,351 --> 00:29:15,185
are of course, the director’s shots…

403
00:29:15,186 --> 00:29:16,821
the jump scares, all those moments.

404
00:29:17,088 --> 00:29:19,022
Since it’s a horror series,

405
00:29:19,023 --> 00:29:21,925
we’ll do our best to make you scared,

406
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:24,862
to make you jump out of your seats,

407
00:29:24,863 --> 00:29:27,097
and just have a really fun time.

408
00:29:27,098 --> 00:29:29,600
You should watch Balik Eskwela

409
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:30,368
on Viva One

410
00:29:30,369 --> 00:29:33,670
because it’s not just about horror.

411
00:29:33,671 --> 00:29:37,541
The story is also about friendship,

412
00:29:37,542 --> 00:29:39,710
a daughter’s love for her mother,

413
00:29:39,711 --> 00:29:40,878
and of course,

414
00:29:40,879 --> 00:29:43,580
you’ll learn something about

415
00:29:43,581 --> 00:29:45,883
valuing the people around you

416
00:29:45,884 --> 00:29:48,119
while they’re still with you.

417
00:29:53,224 --> 00:29:54,559
You’re so beautiful.

418
00:30:05,236 --> 00:30:07,772
I couldn’t hold your hand
when you needed me most.

419
00:30:08,339 --> 00:30:12,409
So, Bahay-bahayan—it’s a story
about a mother and daughter.

420
00:30:12,410 --> 00:30:15,245
Not just them, actually…
It’s about family too.

421
00:30:15,246 --> 00:30:18,616
Siblings, and the love
of a grandmother.

422
00:30:20,819 --> 00:30:23,521
The conflict between mother and daughter.

423
00:30:24,322 --> 00:30:28,525
I honestly feel like
so many people will relate.

424
00:30:28,526 --> 00:30:36,526
Because the story really focuses
on a child searching for a mother’s love.

425
00:30:38,870 --> 00:30:42,105
Not realizing that she’s
so consumed by her own pain…

426
00:30:42,106 --> 00:30:46,477
She doesn’t see that her mom
is fighting battles of her own.

427
00:31:03,361 --> 00:31:08,031
This episode of Bahay-bahayan
is especially beautiful

428
00:31:08,032 --> 00:31:11,235
because it’s about a mother...

429
00:31:11,236 --> 00:31:14,638
A single mom who’s working abroad.

430
00:31:14,639 --> 00:31:18,775
An OFW in London.

431
00:31:18,776 --> 00:31:26,383
And you know how it is
with single moms overseas…

432
00:31:26,384 --> 00:31:34,384
Clara, my character in this anthology,
carry the weight for her kids.

433
00:31:35,660 --> 00:31:40,230
She leaves her two children
with her own mother,

434
00:31:40,231 --> 00:31:41,531
their Lola Estrella.

435
00:31:41,532 --> 00:31:48,872
Ashtine plays Blessie
In this anthology,

436
00:31:48,873 --> 00:31:50,308
And the other child is Agatha.

437
00:32:06,190 --> 00:32:12,029
Blessie is brave.
She’s independent.

438
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:20,030
And maybe… the only difference is—
Because of all the pain she felt,

439
00:32:24,976 --> 00:32:27,311
because she’s so focused
on her own hurt,

440
00:32:27,312 --> 00:32:32,182
she forgets to stay respectful
toward the person she’s angry at.

441
00:32:32,183 --> 00:32:37,521
I relate to Blessie in that way.

442
00:32:37,522 --> 00:32:42,025
She carries this sharpness in her— because
she longs for her family to feel whole.

443
00:32:42,026 --> 00:32:46,430
And me too…

444
00:32:46,431 --> 00:32:48,498
I’ve always wanted something simple.
Like eating together at the same table.

445
00:32:48,499 --> 00:32:55,907
Or going to little fairs, you’re
just enjoying, as long as you’re together.

446
00:32:57,475 --> 00:32:59,843
The hardships,

447
00:32:59,844 --> 00:33:06,817
the love,
the pain of being a mother...

448
00:33:06,818 --> 00:33:09,119
whether you’re single or not.

449
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:13,357
Once you’re a mom,
It’s never easy.

450
00:33:13,358 --> 00:33:15,826
Ate Vi once told me this
when I was younger.

451
00:33:15,827 --> 00:33:17,160
My own mom told me too.

452
00:33:17,161 --> 00:33:19,796
You know how parents always say,

453
00:33:19,797 --> 00:33:23,800
“When you become a mother,
when you become a parent one day,

454
00:33:23,801 --> 00:33:27,804
you’ll understand what we’re saying.
You’ll feel it too.”

455
00:33:27,805 --> 00:33:31,808
Especially when you talk back,
when you try to reason out.

456
00:33:31,809 --> 00:33:33,377
Because answering back
and reasoning out...

457
00:33:33,378 --> 00:33:34,644
those two are very different.

458
00:33:34,645 --> 00:33:40,050
Of course, we adjusted things too.

459
00:33:40,051 --> 00:33:46,089
It was 2000 back then—
Now it’s 2026.

460
00:33:46,090 --> 00:33:48,425
That’s 26 years after Anak.

461
00:33:48,426 --> 00:33:50,694
So much has changed.

462
00:33:50,695 --> 00:33:55,365
There’s video calls now.
Parenting styles are different.

463
00:33:55,366 --> 00:33:57,901
Kids today are different too.

464
00:33:57,902 --> 00:34:03,206
And if she chooses
to go back to school,

465
00:34:03,207 --> 00:34:05,642
it might not be that easy for her anymore.

466
00:34:05,643 --> 00:34:13,183
“Yes. Fish. You know that’s her favorite.
You remember, Ate?”

467
00:34:13,184 --> 00:34:16,853
You know… Earlier, I
was holding back tears.

468
00:34:16,854 --> 00:34:21,691
While delivering my lines,
I kept stumbling over my words.

469
00:34:21,692 --> 00:34:25,262
Because I was trying
to read with emotion...

470
00:34:25,263 --> 00:34:27,631
but also trying
to control my own.

471
00:34:27,632 --> 00:34:29,332
I felt shy about crying.

472
00:34:29,333 --> 00:34:32,002
They might say, “Are you crying already?”

473
00:34:32,003 --> 00:34:36,740
But it’s so beautiful.
The story is so beautiful.

474
00:34:36,741 --> 00:34:41,845
It’s short, but it feels complete.

475
00:34:41,846 --> 00:34:44,515
A beautiful, beautiful story.

476
00:34:45,383 --> 00:34:50,520
I even said its sad that this could’ve been
a full-length film.

477
00:34:50,521 --> 00:34:55,725
That’s how intense it is.
That’s how beautifully made it is.

478
00:34:55,726 --> 00:35:01,731
When I read the script,
One read-through was enough.

479
00:35:01,732 --> 00:35:08,472
I read it once since I
didn’t want to feel it yet.

480
00:35:08,473 --> 00:35:11,609
I told myself that
I’ll let it all out on set.

481
00:35:14,045 --> 00:35:15,645
“You’re such a disrespectful child!”

482
00:35:15,646 --> 00:35:16,447
“What?!”

483
00:35:16,448 --> 00:35:24,448
“Water! Water!
Tissue!”

484
00:35:27,558 --> 00:35:29,826
I was so excited when I found out.

485
00:35:29,827 --> 00:35:32,629
I’d be working with Miss Claudine Barretto.

486
00:35:32,630 --> 00:35:35,165
I felt nervous..

487
00:35:35,166 --> 00:35:37,267
But more than nerves,
it was excitement.

488
00:35:37,268 --> 00:35:43,273
Im so excited for the experience.
For what I’d learn from the journey.

489
00:35:43,274 --> 00:35:47,445
From this episode,
and from Miss Claudine herself.

490
00:35:51,516 --> 00:35:59,516
Blessie is already over 18,
so the paperwork process was a bit tricky.

491
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:04,294
“Blessie, look, it also has furniture!”

492
00:36:04,295 --> 00:36:05,362
Oh my gosh.

493
00:36:05,363 --> 00:36:08,633
Ashtine is an actress.

494
00:36:10,034 --> 00:36:13,069
She is very, very good.

495
00:36:13,070 --> 00:36:15,472
Intense,

496
00:36:15,473 --> 00:36:16,706
passionate,

497
00:36:16,707 --> 00:36:19,343
hungry actress.

498
00:36:20,378 --> 00:36:22,012
She is an Actress.

499
00:36:22,013 --> 00:36:24,348
No one could’ve done it better.

500
00:36:25,917 --> 00:36:31,621
I had no background on her,
Just one video I saw.

501
00:36:31,622 --> 00:36:36,626
And she gets it.
She understands.

502
00:36:36,627 --> 00:36:38,929
She’s a smart actress.

503
00:36:38,930 --> 00:36:42,566
It’s rare to find that now.

504
00:36:42,567 --> 00:36:47,837
Even when she’s juggling so
many other projects aside from this…

505
00:36:47,838 --> 00:36:50,507
I expected her to be tired.

506
00:36:50,508 --> 00:36:52,943
But she shows no sign of it..

507
00:36:52,944 --> 00:36:55,812
She’s competitive, and at the same time.

508
00:36:55,813 --> 00:36:58,081
She’s competitive, and at the same time.

509
00:36:58,082 --> 00:37:01,301
She gives you your moment.

510
00:37:01,326 --> 00:37:05,722
And wow.

511
00:37:05,723 --> 00:37:13,230
Ashtine—she is an actress.

512
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:15,031
And then everything starts
to unravel.

513
00:37:15,032 --> 00:37:18,468
As a mother, your first instinct
is to win your child back.

514
00:37:18,469 --> 00:37:20,604
That’s the point of the mother.

515
00:37:20,605 --> 00:37:22,974
She’s not a bad person.

516
00:37:29,242 --> 00:37:30,743
She’s incredibly hands-on.

517
00:37:30,776 --> 00:37:37,448
Even with my makeup,
She checks my skin.

518
00:37:37,488 --> 00:37:39,756
The wardrobe, the earrings—
Everything.

519
00:37:39,757 --> 00:37:42,259
I was amazed.

520
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:46,998
Because I felt like It helped me
understand my character even more.

521
00:37:53,237 --> 00:37:55,005
“Direk, is this the part where we sit?”

522
00:37:55,006 --> 00:37:56,006
“Not yet.”

523
00:37:56,007 --> 00:38:01,444
“Our house was hit by a storm.
Your sister got sick. Yes!”

524
00:38:01,445 --> 00:38:05,448
The highlight really was the slap.

525
00:38:05,449 --> 00:38:07,318
The confrontation.

526
00:38:08,929 --> 00:38:16,702
But through the whole
show you’ll see the build-up.

527
00:38:16,727 --> 00:38:19,287
The anger. The pain.

528
00:38:19,312 --> 00:38:23,582
And both sides rightfully sow.

529
00:38:23,607 --> 00:38:31,768
There are reasons why
the mother is like that.

530
00:38:32,877 --> 00:38:34,844
Why is Clara like that.

531
00:38:34,845 --> 00:38:39,816
Why Blessie reacts that way.

532
00:38:39,817 --> 00:38:47,817
So when the confrontation
finally happens… it hurts.

533
00:38:53,364 --> 00:38:55,365
I thought I was about to faint.

534
00:38:55,366 --> 00:38:58,168
It’s different when you’re already a mother.

535
00:38:58,169 --> 00:38:59,737
And you’re playing a role like that.

536
00:39:02,673 --> 00:39:05,208
Thank God
I’m not going through that same scene.

537
00:39:05,209 --> 00:39:07,477
And I pray I will never have to
experience that with my children.

538
00:39:07,478 --> 00:39:09,546
Of course, I just lost my mom.

539
00:39:09,547 --> 00:39:15,552
So the first sequence we shot
was the last scene at the cemetery.

540
00:39:16,125 --> 00:39:19,539
How do you do that?

541
00:39:20,015 --> 00:39:22,350
How do you do that at the Cemetery?

542
00:39:22,469 --> 00:39:27,110
It was not even a week
since we buried my mom.

543
00:39:27,135 --> 00:39:30,438
Then I see the name
“Estrella” on the tombstone.

544
00:39:30,568 --> 00:39:32,035
Lord…

545
00:39:32,036 --> 00:39:37,941
And the birthday was March 29.
Rico’s death anniversary.

546
00:39:37,942 --> 00:39:39,409
I asked them,

547
00:39:39,410 --> 00:39:41,797
“Did you plan this? Are
you trying to hurt me?”

548
00:39:43,314 --> 00:39:46,007
The writer said no.

549
00:39:46,032 --> 00:39:53,274
They made the tombstone
back in September 2025.

550
00:39:53,591 --> 00:39:54,425
I asked again,

551
00:39:54,426 --> 00:39:57,127
“Did no one really know about this?”

552
00:39:57,268 --> 00:39:59,203
None. No one knew.

553
00:40:00,469 --> 00:40:03,333
And it hurt.

554
00:40:03,334 --> 00:40:07,000
The kind of pain that
takes your breath away.

555
00:40:11,157 --> 00:40:14,844
Maybe because I never
cried when my mom passed.

556
00:40:14,845 --> 00:40:19,949
So in that cemetery scene,
I let everything out.

557
00:40:19,950 --> 00:40:22,952
And I’m grateful to Direk,
to the staff,

558
00:40:22,953 --> 00:40:27,157
to our DOP, to Ashtine.

559
00:40:27,158 --> 00:40:30,660
We carried it through.

560
00:40:30,661 --> 00:40:33,931
And I hope that’s what the audience feels.

561
00:40:34,975 --> 00:40:36,709
Will they cry?

562
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:39,335
I think they will.

563
00:40:39,336 --> 00:40:41,493
The tears will be overwhelming.

564
00:40:41,518 --> 00:40:43,919
Because earlier, even we’re just
reading it, I was already tearing up.

565
00:40:43,944 --> 00:40:45,878
I was really just holding it in.

566
00:40:45,903 --> 00:40:49,840
Maybe I’m just being Over reacting…
but it’s moving.

567
00:40:49,865 --> 00:40:51,078
It’s so beautiful.

568
00:40:51,103 --> 00:40:53,016
And I feel like
people will have many

569
00:40:53,041 --> 00:40:56,516
realizations to get
from this, and to learn.

570
00:40:56,541 --> 00:41:02,125
Like my character who realizes too late
that she was so focused on her own pain

571
00:41:02,414 --> 00:41:05,602
that she was becoming the
person who once hurt me.

572
00:41:21,278 --> 00:41:23,413
Hello, I’m Claudine Barretto,

573
00:41:23,414 --> 00:41:29,953
And I’d like to invite you
to watch Bahay-Bahayan

574
00:41:29,954 --> 00:41:31,754
from the Ashtine Anthology.

575
00:41:31,755 --> 00:41:34,190
Coming soon on Viva One.

576
00:41:34,191 --> 00:41:36,326
Hi guys, I’m Ashtine Olviga,

577
00:41:36,327 --> 00:41:40,230
And I’m inviting you all
to watch my anthology.

578
00:41:40,231 --> 00:41:47,270
The other episodes are romance,
We have horror,

579
00:41:47,271 --> 00:41:48,838
we have comedy,

580
00:41:48,839 --> 00:41:52,108
and of course, this drama,
Bahay-Bahayan.

581
00:41:52,109 --> 00:41:53,844
Please watch it on Viva One.

582
00:42:02,653 --> 00:42:05,523
I hope you’ll like my
performances here. And...

583
00:42:05,756 --> 00:42:06,756
I hope...

584
00:42:07,700 --> 00:42:11,604
You know, it’s like they watched me grow.

585
00:42:11,629 --> 00:42:15,732
In this industry. So I’m really happy
that they’re here to support me.

586
00:42:15,733 --> 00:42:20,770
And I believe they’re one of God’s
instruments for me to reach my deams.

587
00:42:20,771 --> 00:42:25,042
So thank you for your never ending support.

588
00:42:29,255 --> 00:42:34,022
Hey, guys! Please watch the Ashtine
anthology series. Only on Viva One.
